d the OpenClaw Gateway to apply the new configuration\n- [x] Identified a new error after configuration change: missing API key for the `local-gpu` provider\n- [x] Located the error: `local-gpu` provider configuration in `openclaw.json` has an empty `apiKey` value\n- [x] Checked `auth-profiles.json` in `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/` and confirmed the file exists, with an existing `local-gpu:default` auth entry that also uses an empty key\n- [x] Confirmed there is no root-level `auth-profiles.json` in `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/`\n- [x] Checked the full `local-gpu` provider configuration in `openclaw.json`\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Analyze the `local-gpu` provider configuration to resolve the missing API key error\n\n### Blocked\n- Agent startup fails because of missing API key configuration for the `local-gpu` provider\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Fix model identifier instead of switching to Volcano Engine**: The user's qwen model is already configured correctly under `local-gpu` provider, only the model ID used was incorrect, so corrected the configuration instead of switching to the Volcano Engine model (user confirmed they want to fix the current model first before switching)\n- **Directly modify the openclaw.json configuration file**: Corrected the main agent model setting via direct file edit after failed patching attempts\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Analyze the retrieved full `local-gpu` provider configuration to determine the correct API key configuration for local deployment\n2. Update the configuration to resolve the missing API key error, then restart OpenClaw Gateway to test the fix\n\n## Critical Context\n- User is working with the `openclaw-control-ui` service (metadata label and id: `openclaw-control-ui`)\n- User's custom model: qwen3.5 35b, attempted original model identifier: `qwen/qwen3.5-35b-a3b`\n- Original error: `FailoverError: Unknown model: qwen/qwen3.5-35b-a3b` - the model identifier was incorrect\n- Correct full model ID: `local