h back to the original Volcano Engine model, revert the configuration to `custom-ark-cn-beijing-volces-com/ark-code-latest`\n- Read files:\n  - `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n  - `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`\n- Modified/created files:\n  - `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n  - `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json`\n- Gateway restart after creating root `auth-profiles.json` completed successfully, pid 64036\n- The missing API key error is fully resolved, Gateway is now running normally\n- The `qwen/qwen3.5-35b-a3b` model is correctly defined under the `local-gpu` provider in the configuration\n- The \"model not allowed\" error is fully resolved after adding the model to the allowlist\n- New current active error: `client POST http://127.0.0.1:52001/v1/chat/completions: EOF` - the OpenClaw Gateway cannot connect to the local model endpoint\n- The configured `local-gpu` provider endpoint is `http://127.0.0.1:52001/v1`\n- `sudo lsof -i :52001` returned no results, confirming no process is listening on port 52001, which is the root cause of the EOF connection error\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"bb7e3a5d","tokensBefore":32794,"details":{"readFiles":["/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json","/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json"]},"fromHook":false}
