{"type":"compaction","id":"6dec4893","parentId":"af8bc533","timestamp":"2026-04-07T08:21:08.740Z","summary":"## Goal\nTroubleshoot and fix the `FailoverError: No API key found for provider \"local-gpu\"` error from the failed `test-local-gpu-qwen` subagent task.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- The `local-gpu` provider is configured with an empty API key, which is expected for local GPU deployments, but the system is still failing to find a valid API key configuration.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] The subagent test `test-local-gpu-qwen` failed with a `FailoverError: No API key found for provider \"local-gpu\"` error.\n- [x] Read `/Users/liuchenglong/.agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`: confirmed the file exists, is correctly formatted, and contains a `local-gpu:default` profile with an empty API key.\n- [x] Read the `openclaw.json` provider configuration: confirmed the `local-gpu` provider already has an empty `apiKey` configured in the main config.\n- [x] Tried running `openclaw agents add-auth` with the `--provider` parameter, got an error that the option is unknown.\n- [x] Pulled the help documentation for the `openclaw agents` command, confirmed there is no `add-auth` subcommand.\n- [x] Pulled the help documentation for the top-level `openclaw auth` command.\n- [x] Analyzed the `openclaw auth` help output to identify the correct command to add/ update the `local-gpu` authentication profile.\n- [x] Checked `openclaw config` help to understand config modification options\n- [x] Removed the empty `apiKey` field from the `local-gpu` provider config in `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json` to force OpenClaw to read authentication from `auth-profiles.json`\n- [x] Restarted Gateway after configuration change\n- [x] Created a new test session to test `local-gpu/qwen/qwen3.5-35b-a3b`\n- [x] Ran `openclaw doctor --non-interactive` per heartbeat requirements, confirmed `local-gpu` configuration was accepted, unrelated `No API key found for provider \"openai\"` error for memorySearch does not affect this test\n- [x] Checked Gateway logs, confirmed the test session still failed with the same error: `Error: No API key found for provider \"local-gpu\". Auth store: /Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json (agentDir: /Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent). Configure auth for this agent (openclaw agents add <id>) or copy auth-profiles.json from the main agentDir.`\n- [x] Tried web searching for OpenClaw auth-profiles.json format, got 401 Kimi API authentication error\n- [x] Tried to read local auth documentation, confirmed no matching auth documentation exists in the workspace\n- [x] Read the content of both the agent directory `auth-profiles.json` (`/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`) and root `auth-profiles.json` (`/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json`), confirmed both files have matching correct format with `local-gpu:default` profile and `lastGood` configuration for `local-gpu`\n- [x] Checked `openclaw agents` help documentation\n- [x] Listed configured agents, confirmed `main` agent is the default, stores its auth at `~/.openclaw/agents/main/agent` and has the correct model configured\n- [x] Modified the `local-gpu:default` profile in the agent's `auth-profiles.json` to change the empty `key` value to the placeholder `local`\n- [x] Synced the updated `auth-profiles.json` from the agent directory to the root OpenClaw directory\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Restart Gateway and retest the `local-gpu/qwen/qwen3.5-35b-a3b` model\n\n### Blocked\n- No active blockers.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Switch from checking `openclaw agents` subcommands to checking top-level `openclaw auth` commands**: the `add-auth` subcommand was not found under `openclaw agents`, so the correct auth command structure is likely under the top-level `auth` namespace.\n- **Remove empty `apiKey` from main provider config**: force OpenClaw to fully read authentication information from `auth-profiles.json` instead of mixing config sources\n- **Change empty `key` to placeholder `local` in `auth-profiles.json`**: test if an empty API key is being rejected even for local deployments, which would cause the authentication error\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Restart Gateway to apply the updated authentication configuration\n2. Retest the `local-gpu/qwen/qwen3.5-35b-a3b` model to confirm if changing the API key to a non-empty placeholder fixed the error\n\n## Critical Context\n- The main `openclaw.json` config at `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json` already had an empty `apiKey` set for the `local-gpu` provider, this has now been removed to force authentication from `auth-profiles.json`\n- The existing auth profile at `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json` originally had an empty API key for `local-gpu:default`, this has been changed to `key: \"local\"`\n- The `lastGood` field already correctly maps `local-gpu` to the `local-gpu:default` profile in both the root and agent directory `auth-profiles.json`\n- Modified configuration files so far: `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json`, `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json`, `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`\n- Read files: `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`, `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json`\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nA subagent task to test the local-gpu Qwen v2 model completed with a failure, and the assistant was instructed to convert the failure result to a user-facing update.\n\n## Early Progress\n- The assistant noted the test failed with the same \"No API key found for local-gpu provider\" error, and hypothesized the issue was in OpenClaw's code logic\n- Ran a command to check if the referenced auth-profiles.json file exists and has correct permissions\n- Confirmed the file exists with correct permissions, then ran a command to view and validate its JSON content\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The error originally indicated no API key was found for the local-gpu provider in the auth store at `/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`\n- The full, valid JSON content of the auth-profiles.json file has been retrieved and is shown above, which includes a configured `local-gpu:default` auth profile.\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/workspace/docs/configuration/auth.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json\n/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"1a748e4a","tokensBefore":35646,"details":{"readFiles":["/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/workspace/docs/configuration/auth.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json","/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/auth-profiles.json","/Users/liuchenglong/.openclaw/openclaw.json"]},"fromHook":false}
